@node LEVED "Editing levels"

Controlling the level editor is quite simple.

Use the keys Q,A,O,P to move the editing box.
Use the arrow/cursor keys to move the silver arrow.
When the arrow is on the left. Press Up and Down arrows to cycle through
the available "Blokz". Press Space/Enter to place the block on the current
square.
When the arrow is on the right. Press Enter or Space on the time parameter
to change the amount of time available to complete the level. Use the left
and right arrow keys to increase or decrease the amount and press
Enter/Space when finished.
Pressing enter or space on the other parameter lets you choose from a menu
of options, use left or right arrows to cycle through them. Options are:
LOAD, SAVE : Self explanitory.
PLYR : Positions the levels player starting position on the current space
(hi-lited with the box)
INFO : Tells you which level you are editing.
Press Escape to exit this menu without doing anything.

Pressing Escape when no menu is activated quits the editor.

